# I. PURPOSE

Define a universal architecture for extracting structural value from any dense, high-signal book.

This machine converts:

Dense Information  
→ Structural Primitives  
→ Formal Mechanisms  
→ Break Conditions  
→ MVP Set  
→ Reflex Drills  
→ Cross-Domain Transfer Map  

This is not summarization.  
This is structural harvesting.

---

# II. DESIGN AXIOM

A “useful book” contains transferable mechanisms.

Transferable mechanisms include:

- Rules
- Constraints
- Incentive gradients
- Tradeoff structures
- Decision procedures
- Equilibrium conditions
- Failure cases
- Instability triggers

Narrative, persuasion, anecdote, stylistic padding, and rhetorical flourish are discarded unless they introduce a new structural primitive.

---

# III. CORE DATA STRUCTURES

All extraction output is built from four primitive objects.

---

## A. ATOM (Structural Primitive)

Smallest actionable unit.

Fields:

- Name (short identifier)
- Type:
  - Definition
  - Mechanism
  - Constraint
  - Heuristic
  - Procedure
  - Warning
  - Edge Case
- Claim (one-line invariant)
- Formal Expression:
  - Equation
  - IF/THEN/BECAUSE rule
  - Decision rule
  - Boundary condition
- Variables (governing inputs)
- Assumptions
- Break Conditions
- Counterexample (if provided or implied)
- Source Pointer (page / section reference)
- Transfer Map (domains applicable)
- Drill Seed (reflex training entry point)

Every ATOM must reference the book.  
No invented content permitted.

---

## B. CLUSTER (Family)

A group of related ATOMs.

Fields:

- Cluster Name
- Purpose
- Included ATOMs
- Dependency Links (prerequisite ATOMs)

Clusters define conceptual topology.

---

## C. MVP SET (Load-Bearing Beams)

Top ATOMs generating maximum leverage.

Fields:

- MVP List
- Score (see scoring function)
- Replacement Coverage (what other ATOMs it explains)
- Enables (what capabilities it unlocks)

MVPs must be:

- Transferable
- Formalizable
- Decision-impacting

---

## D. DRILL PACK (Reflex Engine)

Training layer derived from MVPs.

Fields per MVP:

- 30-second drill
- 2-minute scenario drill
- Error taxonomy
- Break-spotting drill
- Spaced repetition cue

Goal: convert principle into reflex.

---

# IV. PIPELINE STAGES

---

## Stage 1 — Parse & Segment

- Extract headings and structural sections.
- Build section map.
- Ignore formatting artifacts.

Output: Section Index

---

## Stage 2 — Atomization

For each section, extract only:

- Definitions
- Rules
- Ratios
- Constraints
- Procedures
- Instability triggers
- Explicit warnings

Discard:

- Narrative examples (unless structural)
- Repetition
- Persuasion

Output: Raw ATOM List

---

## Stage 3 — Deduplicate & Normalize

- Merge repeated concepts
- Unify variable names
- Remove semantic duplicates
- Standardize formal expression format

Output: Clean ATOM List

---

## Stage 4 — Formalization

Every ATOM must be reducible to one of:

- Equation
- IF / THEN / BECAUSE
- Boundary condition
- Decision rule
- Tradeoff statement

If it cannot be formalized, downgrade priority.

Output: Formal ATOM List

---

## Stage 5 — Adversarial Break Testing

For each ATOM:

- When does this fail?
- What assumption collapses first?
- What distortion invalidates it?
- What adversary adaptation defeats it?

Add break conditions explicitly.

Output: Break-Conditioned ATOM List

---

## Stage 6 — Clustering + Dependency Graph

Group ATOMs into CLUSTERS.

Construct:

- Conceptual families
- Dependency DAG
- Prerequisite chains

Output:
- Cluster Map
- Dependency Graph

---

## Stage 7 — MVP Selection (Pareto Optimization)

Score each ATOM 0–5 on:

1. Recurrence (frequency across book)
2. Generativity (explains other ATOMs)
3. Decision Impact
4. Transferability
5. Formalizability
6. Break Clarity

Select highest scoring ATOMs with diversity constraint across clusters.

Output: MVP Set

---

## Stage 8 — Compression Layers

Produce three tiers from same truth:

1. Full ATOM Index
2. MVP Sheet (one-liners + equations + breaks)
3. Brain-Slam Page (single page, ultra-dense, no paragraphs)

If new MVPs appear in final 15% of text, repeat scoring.

Extraction is complete when MVP set stabilizes.

---

## Stage 9 — Drill Generation

For each MVP:

Generate:

- 30-second computation or classification drill
- 2-minute scenario drill
- Break-condition identification drill
- Error pattern recognition drill

Drills must be executable without external tools.

---

## Stage 10 — Cross-Domain Transfer Map

For each MVP, map applicability to:

- Markets (Flow / Pressure / Incentive / Power / Belief)
- Governance / institutions
- AI incentives
- Social dynamics
- Negotiation
- Personal systems

If non-transferable, mark explicitly.

Transferability increases structural rank.

