# V. OUTPUT CONTRACT

Each extraction run must produce:

1. ATOM_INDEX_[BOOK]_V001
2. CLUSTERMAP_[BOOK]_V001
3. MVPSET_[BOOK]_V001
4. BRAINSLAM_[BOOK]_V001
5. DRILLPACK_[BOOK]_V001
6. TRANSFERMAP_[BOOK]_V001

No run is complete without all six artifacts.

---

# VI. MODES

## FAST MODE

- Extract ATOMs
- Build MVP Set
- Generate Brain-Slam
- Produce minimal Drill Pack

Skip deep dependency mapping.

---

## FULL MODE

- Full pipeline
- Complete dependency DAG
- Full transfer mapping
- Adversarial stress-testing

---

# VII. QUALITY GATES

1. No invented ATOMs.
2. Every ATOM has source pointer.
3. No summary paragraphs in final outputs.
4. No rhetorical inflation.
5. Every MVP must:
   - Be formalizable
   - Have break condition
   - Be drillable

Failure to meet any gate invalidates extraction.

---

# VIII. COMPLETION CRITERIA

Extraction is complete when:

- MVP Set stable
- No new structural primitives emerge
- Brain-Slam page fits one screen
- Drill Pack executable daily
- Transfer Map populated or marked non-transferable

---

# IX. PHILOSOPHICAL FOUNDATION

Dense books contain compression of experience.

This machine performs second-order compression.

Information → Structure  
Structure → Mechanism  
Mechanism → Constraint  
Constraint → Reflex  

Reading is passive.  
Extraction is architectural.

